name: Taj Mahal
description: Taj Mahal, an ivory-white marble mausoleum located on the southern bank of the river Yamuna in Agra, India. This was commissioned by the Mughal emperor Shah Jahan in 1632 to house the tomb of his favourite wife, Mumtaz Mahal; it also houses the tomb of Shah Jahan. The tomb is the centrepiece of a 17-hectare (42-acre) complex and is included in seven Wonders of the World.
